      nativeForm: 'Not only does agenda-setting theory reveal that media determine which issues citizens think about — it also reveals that the very categories through which issues are understood, the values against which they are evaluated, and the range of solutions that appear politically feasible are themselves the products of representational choices that are rarely made visible to the audiences they affect.',
