      nativeForm: "So thoroughly has cultural capital been naturalised — so completely have the advantages of privileged social positions come to appear as personal qualities of their bearers rather than as the specific inheritances of those positions — that the educational system, which functions as the primary mechanism for its transmission and legitimation, appears to reward individual merit while in fact rewarding cultural preparation.",
      explanation: 'انقلابان متوازيان مع em-dash + جملة نسبية اعتراضية + جملة رئيسية. النبرة: "THOroughly", "NATuralised", "comPLETEly", "ADvantages", "PRIVileged", "INheritances", "TRANSmission", "LEGitimation", "REwarding".',
