      nativeForm: "So thoroughly have international human rights norms been institutionalised — in courts, treaty bodies, special rapporteurs, and the practice of states — that it is no longer possible to understand the international order as simply a system of states interacting in a condition of moral anarchy; what has emerged is something that falls short of a global legal order but significantly exceeds the pure power politics that realist accounts describe.",
