      nativeForm: "So thoroughly has the assumption of secularisation shaped the intellectual frameworks of Western social science that the return of religion to public life has not merely required empirical revision of the secularisation thesis but a more fundamental rethinking of the modernist assumption that rationality and religiosity occupy fundamentally different and incompatible cognitive and motivational spaces.",
