      nativeForm: "Not only does Benjamin's analysis of the aura reveal something important about how mechanical reproduction changes our relationship to art — it also raises, by implication, the question of what we lose when the unique, singular experience of the original artwork is replaced by the democratised but aurally depleted experience of the reproduced copy, and whether what we lose is worth lamenting.",
